<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1947588-do-you-read-claggart-as-gay-closeted--">Do you read Claggart as gay &amp; closeted - hating handsome Billy because he can&#39;t admit to his attraction?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1947588'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15613.Billy_Budd_Sailor">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1947588-do-you-read-claggart-as-gay-closeted--">9 months ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1947588-do-you-read-claggart-as-gay-closeted--">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8394997-dillwynia-peter"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1332831047i/8394997._UX100_CR0,28,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8394997-dillwynia-peter">Dillwynia Peter</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I most certainly considered it as a possibility. Nothing in Billy Budd is a simple layer - there are multilayers and nuances to every action and often<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I most certainly considered it as a possibility. Nothing in Billy Budd is a simple layer - there are multilayers and nuances to every action and often in dialogue and introspection. <br />Claggart has no history, and I suspect this is deliberate and makes him a nobody. In the English Navy, he needed to pander for favours to rise in the ranks. What the basic sailors was considered typical of uneducated animals of the working classes, but officers were gentlemen, and this suddenly is abhorrent both from the religious and societal views. The soup scene is very important and can be taken as a man who is vindictive, or a man sexually frustrated.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1097531" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1097531&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1947588-do-you-read-claggart-as-gay-closeted--%2Fanswers%2F1097531-i-most-certainly">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
