  <span id="freeText10067234899253635621" style="display:none">This is a novella that manages to condense in itself all of Mellvile's larger-than-life tendencies in writing. It might be short, but it contains all the mythological, historical and religious allusions that a fan of Melville would want, completed with a theme of <i>desire</i>. Loved it.</span>
